{"key":"processedPost-26992611","value":{"id":26992611,"first":26992548,"last":26998784,"when":1603122262,"utime":"10/19/20 06:44 PM","content":"Less is more when it comes to grain moisture.&nbsp; If they're too wet, colonization is slowed.&nbsp; I like to do a boil after the soak, and then toss in the strainer until they steam off excess moisture.&nbsp; You want them nearly dry before loading into jars for the sterilizer.<br />The <a href=\"https://www.mushroomvideos.com/Grain-Preparation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">grain prep tek</a> on let's grow mushrooms demonstrates an easy way to get the moisture perfect.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pre PC WBS Moisture Content and Softness"}}